      "date": "2022-05-24 19:11:08.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nI don't think we should revive the dev_rdonly mount option, as it is *not* the same as s normal \"ro\" mount, because \"dev_rdonly\" pretends that writes are succeeding, but throws away the data. I don't think that should be mixed with \"ro\", since that might lead to data loss if someone is accidentally mounting with \"-o ro\" but not getting an \"-EROFS\" error back.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
