        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Arshad Hussain",
          "email": "arshad.hussain@aeoncomputing.com",
          "date": "2022-05-20 13:27:57.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-15873 osd: Make mounting with \"-o rdonly_dev\" work",
        "message": "LU-15873 osd: Make mounting with \"-o rdonly_dev\" work\n\nWhen \"rdonly_dev\" flag is passed at mount time to\nMDS/OSS. This allows MDS/OSS to be mounted read-only.\nThis read-only is granted by dm-flakey's \"drop writes\"\nswitch. That is, it is not \"pure\" read only but only\ndiscards the writes to the device. For ldiskfs-osd\nthis was always returning \"EOPNOTSUPP\". This patch\nremoves the check where EOPNOTSUPP is returned and\nallows the mount to continue.\n\nBefore Patch:\n~~~~~~~~~~~~~\n$ mount.lustre /dev/mapper/mds1_flakey /mnt/lustre-mds1 -o rdonly_dev\nmount.lustre: mount /dev/mapper/mds1_flakey at /mnt/lustre-mds1\nfailed: Operation not supported\n\nAfter Patch:\n~~~~~~~~~~~~\n$ mount.lustre /dev/mapper/mds1_flakey /mnt/lustre-mds1 -o rdonly_dev\n$ mount | grep lustre | grep mds\n/dev/mapper/mds1_flakey on /mnt/lustre-mds1 type lustre\n(ro,svname=lustre-MDT0000,rdonly_dev,mgs,osd=osd-ldiskfs,user_xattr,\nerrors=remount-ro)\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Arshad Hussain <arshad.hussain@aeoncomputing.com>\nChange-Id: If601bfdb9fa9214128b6df4a33124c9dfad63107\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
